Text:
Everything sounds great, so far as I can tell. I'm not an audiophile, so I can't tell the full technical audio qualityâ€”but there don't seem to be skips, or drops in the quality.

As for the album itself, to me, it's more 'songwritery' (ie folk inspired), and Waits has actually shed some of his "Waitsiness" that characterized his past few albums; those who're interested in his eclectic, bluesy, electric sounds will not find so much of that here. It has a more distinctly European flavor. I cannot fault the uploader for this, so A+.
